Implemented the four MUST-FIX items and did not commit.

Changes are in [codetection_data.py](/Users/jakobfaber/Developer/repos/github.com/jakobtfaber/Faber2026/pipeline/flits/batch/codetection_data.py), [codetection_plots.py](/Users/jakobfaber/Developer/repos/github.com/jakobtfaber/Faber2026/pipeline/flits/batch/codetection_plots.py), [codetection_joint.py](/Users/jakobfaber/Developer/repos/github.com/jakobtfaber/Faber2026/pipeline/flits/batch/codetection_joint.py), plus the new focused tests in [test_codetection_data.py](/Users/jakobfaber/Developer/repos/github.com/jakobtfaber/Faber2026/pipeline/tests/test_codetection_data.py).

What changed:
- Audited TOA semantics: `measured_offset_ms` is `CHIME_TOA_400 - DSA_TOA_400`, so the existing CHIME shift by `-offset` is consistent. I documented that residual CHIME/DSA peak separation is intentionally preserved after midpoint centering.
- Capped the last subburst trailing reference at `last_peak + 6 ms` before applying `SUBBURST_PAD_MS = 3.0`, preventing mahi/oran-style long noise tails from owning the right crop.
- Preserved exact requested crop endpoints and pads missing snippet time with `NaN`; the plotter hatches all-NaN no-data time spans instead of showing edge-filled/flat texture.
- Made per-band spectrum normalization active when `per_band_scale=True`; observation plots also use per-band normalized top profiles.

Before/after highlights:
- `mahi`: xlim `(-9.006, 37.199)` -> `(-11.711, 17.711)`, width `46.205 -> 29.423`; left/right pads now `3.000/3.000 ms`.
- `oran`: xlim `(-6.305, 29.005)` -> `(-6.313, 12.313)`, width `35.310 -> 18.627`; left/right pads now `3.000/3.000 ms`.
- `phineas`: xlim stays wide because the peaks are genuinely separated (`±12.373 ms`), but padding is exact and DSA no-data is hatched instead of edge-filled.
- `whitney`: xlim `(-15.169, 16.813)` -> `(-16.503, 16.831)`; this restores the missing 3 ms left pad and hatches CHIME no-data.
- `isha`: xlim/peaks are essentially unchanged, but CHIME now appears in normalized spectrum/profile instead of being dwarfed by DSA.

